# Game Domain

## Governance

This rule is **priority 3** in the rule hierarchy. Supreme authority: `docs/architecture/ai-constitution.md`.

| Document | Path |
|----------|------|
| AI Constitution | `docs/architecture/ai-constitution.md` |
| Workflow | `.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc` |
| Universal agent instructions | `AGENTS.md` |
| Project context skill | `.claude/skills/project-context/SKILL.md` |
| Project vision | `docs/architecture/project-vision.md` |

Game rules must not leak outside domain/application. Major game features require planning per `workflow.mdc`.

## Purpose

Encode the football draft/simulation domain model for draft.io backend modules. Each module is a **bounded context** with a defined responsibility. Game rules live in domain entities and value objects — not in controllers, DTOs, or repositories.

## Required Behavior

### Domain Modules

| Module | Type | Responsibility |
|--------|------|----------------|
| `positions` | Vocabulary | 15 valid position codes (GK, CB, ST, etc.) |
| `players` | Aggregate | Player cards: name, position, overall rating |
| `formations` | Templates | Tactical layouts with 11 slots and allowed positions |
| `teams` | Aggregate | Starting eleven, formation code, manager (future) |
| `nations` | Aggregate | National identity for players and leagues |
| `leagues` | Aggregate | Groups of teams within a nation and season |
| `draft` | Aggregate (future) | Draft room logic and pick order |
| `lobbies` | Aggregate (future) | Lobby management and matchmaking |
| `matches` | Aggregate (future) | Match scheduling and results |
| `simulation` | Service (future) | Match engine and chemistry calculations |

### Aggregate Rules

- **Entities** extend `Entity<TId>` with private constructors and factory methods (`create`, `reconstitute`).
- **Value objects** extend `ValueObject<TProps>` with validation in `static create()`.
- **Invariants** enforced inside the aggregate — reject invalid state at creation/mutation time.
- **IDs** are typed value objects (`PlayerId`, `TeamId`), not raw strings in domain.

### Cross-Module References

- Hold foreign aggregates by **ID only**: `playerIds: readonly string[]`, `formationCode: string`.
- Import other modules' **value objects** in domain when needed (e.g., `Position` in `Player`).
- Never import another module's **entity** into your domain layer.
- Application use cases validate references exist before assignment.

### Position System

- 15 positions defined in `positions` module: `ALL_PLAYER_POSITIONS` in shared-types.
- `Position.create(code)` validates against allowed codes.
- Formations define slots with `allowedPositions` per slot.

### Player Cards

- `displayName`: 1–100 characters, non-empty.
- `overallRating`: integer 1–99.
- `position`: one of 15 valid codes.

### Teams & Starting Eleven

- Exactly 11 player slots in `StartingEleven` value object.
- Each slot maps to a position compatible with the chosen formation.
- `formationCode` references a predefined formation template.
- `chemistryScore` and `teamOverall` reserved for future calculation (currently `null`).

### Formations

- Predefined templates stored in-memory (`formation-templates.ts`).
- Each formation has a unique code (e.g., `4-3-3`) and 11 slots.
- Slots specify allowed positions — validation in `FormationSlot` value object.

### Future Flows (Design Targets)

**Draft:** Lobby → draft room → picks assign `PlayerId` to `Team.startingEleven` → `DraftCompleted` event.

**Match:** Schedule → load teams by ID → resolve players → apply chemistry → run simulation → store result.

## Forbidden Patterns

- Storing full `Player` objects inside `Team` domain entity.
- Position validation via string comparison in controllers.
- Overall rating bounds checked only in DTO, not in `OverallRating` value object.
- Game rules scattered across infrastructure mappers.
- Mutable collections exposed from entities (return copies or readonly arrays).
- Skipping `reconstitute` factory when loading from persistence.
- Business logic in NestJS modules or DTOs.

## Good Examples

```typescript
// domain/value-objects/overall-rating.vo.ts
export class OverallRating extends ValueObject<{ value: number }> {
  static create(value: number): OverallRating {
    if (!Number.isInteger(value) || value < 1 || value > 99) {
      throw new InvalidOverallRatingError(value);
    }
    return new OverallRating({ value });
  }
}
```

```typescript
// domain/entities/player.entity.ts
export class Player extends Entity<PlayerId> {
  static create(props: CreatePlayerProps): Player {
    return new Player({ ...props, createdAt: new Date(), updatedAt: new Date() });
  }

  static reconstitute(props: PlayerProps): Player {
    return new Player(props);
  }

  updatePosition(position: Position): void {
    this._position = position;
    this._updatedAt = new Date();
  }
}
```

```typescript
// teams domain — reference players by ID
export interface TeamProps {
  readonly id: TeamId;
  readonly name: TeamName;
  readonly playerIds: readonly string[];
  readonly formationCode: string;
}
```

## Bad Examples

```typescript
// BAD: foreign entity embedded in aggregate
import { Player } from '../../players/domain/entities/player.entity';

export class Team extends Entity<TeamId> {
  private readonly _startingEleven: Player[];
}
```

```typescript
// BAD: validation only in DTO
export class CreatePlayerDto {
  @IsInt() @Min(1) @Max(99) overallRating: number;
  // No OverallRating value object — domain can be bypassed
}
```

```typescript
// BAD: public constructor bypassing invariants
export class Player extends Entity<PlayerId> {
  constructor(public name: string, public rating: number) {
    super(PlayerId.create('any'));
  }
}
```

## Checklist

- [ ] Module responsibility matches the domain table above
- [ ] Entities use `create` and `reconstitute` factories
- [ ] Value objects validate in `static create()`
- [ ] Cross-module references use IDs, not embedded entities
- [ ] Game invariants enforced in domain, not presentation
- [ ] Position and rating rules use shared value objects
- [ ] Domain errors defined in `domain/errors/` with `code` property
- [ ] Future fields (`chemistryScore`, etc.) documented as nullable placeholders
